description*.en: The pressure exerted by the weight of the air above it at any point on the earth's surface. At sea level the atmosphere will support a column of mercury about $760 mm$ high. This decreases with increasing altitude. The standard value for the atmospheric pressure at sea level in SI units is $101,325 pascals$.
